js.core.JsClass

Packages that use JsClass
js.core Opaque classes simulating core JavaScript objects. 
js.dom Opaque classes and interfaces simulating client-side DOM. 
js.user Opaque classes simulating client-side JavaScript objects.

Fields in js.core with type parameters of type JsClass
static JsFunction.Member<JsClass> JsClass.constructor
          An opaque static field defining a member that is named by the field name without a qualifying member and to access the property of the name on an object.
static JsFunction.Member<JsClass> JsClass.valueOf
          An opaque static field defining a member that is named by the field name without a qualifying member and to access the property of the name on an object.
 

Methods in js.core that return JsClass
 JsClass JsClass.and(JsClass other)
          Logical AND operation, resembling that of JavaScript, performs the Boolean AND operation on the two values: it returns true if and only if both its first operand and its second operand are true.
 JsClass JsClass.cond(java.lang.Object test, JsClass other)
          Conditional operation, resembling the ternary operator of JavaScript, returns the second operand if the first operand evaluates to true; Returns the third operand, otherwise.
 JsClass JsClass.or(JsClass other)
          Logical OR operation, resembling that of JavaScript, performs the Boolean OR operation on the two values: it returns true if either the first operand or the second operand is true, or if both are true.
 JsClass JsClass.valueOf()
          Returns the primitive value associated with the current instance, if there is one.
 JsClass JsClass.var()
          Simply returns the current boolean instance.
 JsClass JsClass.Member.with()
          Evaluates a property, represented by the current member instance, of the JavaScript global object, that is, evaluates the member to a global identifier.
 JsClass JsClass.Member.with(ObjectLike o)
          Evaluates the property, represented by the current member instance, of the argument object.
 

Methods in js.core with parameters of type JsClass
 JsClass JsClass.and(JsClass other)
          Logical AND operation, resembling that of JavaScript, performs the Boolean AND operation on the two values: it returns true if and only if both its first operand and its second operand are true.
 JsClass JsClass.cond(java.lang.Object test, JsClass other)
          Conditional operation, resembling the ternary operator of JavaScript, returns the second operand if the first operand evaluates to true; Returns the third operand, otherwise.
 JsClass JsClass.or(JsClass other)
          Logical OR operation, resembling that of JavaScript, performs the Boolean OR operation on the two values: it returns true if either the first operand or the second operand is true, or if both are true.
